        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 28 at 8:16AM EST by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>HAZARDS...A lake effect snow band accompanied by winds of up to 30
mph which can rapidly reduce visibility to less than one mile.

LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 815 AM EST, a lake effect snow band was 9
miles southwest of Sacandaga Campground, or 17 miles north of
Gloversville moving east at 40 MPH.

THIS LAKE EFFECT SNOW BAND WILL BE NEAR...
Sacandaga Campground around 825 AM EST.
Day Center around 840 AM EST.
Lake Luzerne-Hadley around 850 AM EST.
Lake Luzerne Campground around 855 AM EST.
Glens Falls North around 900 AM EST.
Glens Falls and West Glens Falls around 905 AM EST.

This includes Interstate 87 between exits 16 and 22.

Snow rates could reach a half an inch to an inch an hours reduce
visibility briefly to a half mile or less.

SAFETY INFO...
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down and allow extra
time to reach your destination.
</description>
